# ============================================================
# Globe AMS — 06. Multi-Tenancy Isolation Tests
# ============================================================
# Verifies that EF Core global query filters enforce strict
# row-level tenant isolation. A user authenticated for Tenant A
# must NEVER access Tenant B's data, even with known GUIDs.
#
# Architecture reminder:
#   TenantResolver reads "tenantId" from JWT claim (priority 1)
#   or X-Tenant-Id header (priority 2, unauthenticated routes only).
#
#   AppDbContext global query filter on all tenant-scoped entities:
#     HasQueryFilter(e => !e.IsDeleted && (tenantId == null || e.TenantId == tenantId))
#
#   tenantId == null only when TenantResolver returns null
#   (i.e., no JWT + no X-Tenant-Id header → bypasses filter for super-admin).
#
# ============================================================
# PREREQUISITES:
#   ✓ alpha-clinic and beta-spa tenants created (02_tenant-management.http)
#   ✓ Alice registered + verified in alpha-clinic, logged in → alphaAdminToken
#   ✓ Bob registered + verified in beta-spa, logged in → betaAdminToken
#   ✓ Services created in each tenant (04_services.http)
#   ✓ At least one appointment created in Globe tenant (05_appointments.http)
# ============================================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5006

@globeAdminToken  = PASTE_GLOBE_ADMIN_JWT_HERE
@globeTenantId    = PASTE_GLOBE_TENANT_ID_HERE
@globeApptId      = PASTE_GLOBE_APPT_ID_HERE   # from 05_appointments.http step 1

@alphaTenantId    = PASTE_ALPHA_TENANT_ID_HERE
@alphaAdminToken  = PASTE_ALPHA_ADMIN_JWT_HERE
@alphaApptId      = PASTE_ALPHA_APPT_ID_HERE   # appointment in alpha-clinic (if created)

@betaTenantId     = PASTE_BETA_TENANT_ID_HERE
@betaAdminToken   = PASTE_BETA_ADMIN_JWT_HERE

@clientToken      = PASTE_GLOBE_CLIENT_JWT_HERE  # Jane's Client token (globe tenant)


### =================================================================
### SECTION A — Tenant-Scoped Login Isolation
### =================================================================

### A1. Globe admin logs in via wrong tenant slug → 403
# Correct credentials, wrong tenant → AppUser.TenantId mismatch
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@globe.com",
  "password": "Admin@123!",
  "tenantSlug": "beta-spa"
}

###
# ❌ Expected 403 Forbidden — "User does not belong to this tenant."
# ✓ Identity resolves the user, then AppUser FK check fails:
#   appUser.TenantId = globe ≠ beta-spa
# ✓ Credentials alone are not enough — tenant membership is required.

### A2. Alice (alpha) logs in via globe slug → 403
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@alphaclinic.com",
  "password": "Alpha@123!",
  "tenantSlug": "globe"
}

###
# ❌ Expected 403 — alice@alphaclinic.com belongs to alpha-clinic, not globe

### A3. Login with non-existent tenant → 404
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@globe.com",
  "password": "Admin@123!",
  "tenantSlug": "fake-xyz"
}

###
# ❌ Expected 404 — tenant not found before credentials are even validated


### =================================================================
### SECTION B — JWT-Based EF Query Filter (Appointments)
### =================================================================

### B1. Globe admin reads ALPHA appointments (expect empty array)
# JWT: tenantId=globe → EF filter: WHERE TenantId=globe
# Route param: alphaTenantId → handler queries WHERE TenantId=alpha
# Combined: 0 rows returned (globe ≠ alpha)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/tenant/{{alphaTenantId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{globeAdminToken}}

###
# ✅ Expected 200 with [] — EF query filter blocks cross-tenant read
# The globe JWT + alpha route param = no matching rows

### B2. Alpha admin reads GLOBE appointments (expect empty array)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/tenant/{{globeTenantId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{alphaAdminToken}}

###
# ✅ Expected 200 with [] — alpha JWT + globe route param = no matching rows

### B3. Beta admin reads GLOBE appointments (expect empty array)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/tenant/{{globeTenantId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{betaAdminToken}}

###
# ✅ Expected 200 with []

### B4. Alpha admin reads BETA appointments (expect empty array)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/tenant/{{betaTenantId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{alphaAdminToken}}

###
# ✅ Expected 200 with []


### =================================================================
### SECTION C — Cross-Tenant ID Guessing (Single Resource)
### =================================================================

### C1. Alpha admin fetches Globe appointment by known ID → 404
# Even if Alice knows the Globe appointment's GUID, EF filter blocks it.
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/{{globeApptId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{alphaAdminToken}}

###
# ❌ Expected 404 Not Found
# EF filter: WHERE TenantId=alpha → 0 rows → NotFoundException

### C2. Globe admin fetches Alpha appointment by ID → 404
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/{{alphaApptId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{globeAdminToken}}

###
# ❌ Expected 404 Not Found
# ✓ Cross-tenant GUID guessing is blocked at the database filter layer

### C3. Alpha admin tries to CONFIRM a Globe appointment → 404
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/{{globeApptId}}/confirm
Authorization: Bearer {{alphaAdminToken}}

###
# ❌ Expected 404 — appointment not visible to alpha → cannot be mutated


### =================================================================
### SECTION D — X-Tenant-Id Header Behavior
### =================================================================
# TenantResolver resolution order:
#   1. JWT "tenantId" claim (authenticated requests)
#   2. X-Tenant-Id header (unauthenticated requests)
#   3. null (no filter → super-admin bypass)

### D1. Get Globe services via X-Tenant-Id header (unauthenticated)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/services/tenant/{{globeTenantId}}
X-Tenant-Id: {{globeTenantId}}

###
# ✅ Expected 200 — Globe services returned
# No JWT → TenantResolver uses X-Tenant-Id header → EF filter applied correctly

### D2. Get Alpha services via X-Tenant-Id header
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/services/tenant/{{alphaTenantId}}
X-Tenant-Id: {{alphaTenantId}}

###
# ✅ Expected 200 — Alpha services only

### D3. X-Tenant-Id with fake GUID (expect empty array)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/services/tenant/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
X-Tenant-Id: 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

###
# ✅ Expected 200 with [] — no services for nonexistent tenantId

### D4. JWT tenantId overrides X-Tenant-Id header (authenticated request)
# Globe admin JWT has tenantId=globe. Header says alpha.
# JWT WINS → globe filter applied → globe's appointments returned only.
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/tenant/{{globeTenantId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{globeAdminToken}}
X-Tenant-Id: {{alphaTenantId}}

###
# ✅ Expected 200 — Globe appointments (JWT tenantId takes precedence)
# ✓ Header spoofing cannot escalate a JWT-authenticated request


### =================================================================
### SECTION E — Write Operations: tenantId Always From JWT
### =================================================================

### E1. Globe admin creates appointment — tenantId from JWT, NOT body
# The CreateAppointmentCommand does not accept tenantId in the request body.
# It always uses ICurrentUserService.TenantId (from JWT claim).
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{globeAdminToken}}

{
  "serviceId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001",
  "staffId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001",
  "startTime": "2026-07-01T10:00:00Z",
  "notes": "TenantId injection test — id in notes is ignored"
}

###
# Response tenantId will equal globeTenantId regardless of any IDs in the body.
# (Request may fail with 404 if serviceId/staffId don't exist — that's fine,
#  the point is tenantId cannot be overridden via request payload.)

### E2. Globe admin creates service — tenantId from JWT (not body)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/services
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{globeAdminToken}}

{
  "name": "Isolation Proof Service",
  "description": "This will be created in GLOBE tenant regardless of alpha context",
  "durationMinutes": 15,
  "price": 5.00
}

###
# ✅ Expected 201 — tenantId in response = globeTenantId (not alphaTenantId)
# ✓ Write path enforces tenant isolation through JWT extraction, not trust in client input


### =================================================================
### SECTION F — Role + Tenant Combined Authorization
### =================================================================

### F1. Client role (globe) tries to confirm appointment → 403
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/{{globeApptId}}/confirm
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}

###
# ❌ Expected 403 — role "Client" is not in [TenantAdmin, Staff]

### F2. Client role (globe) tries to complete appointment → 403
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/{{globeApptId}}/complete
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}

###
# ❌ Expected 403

### F3. Alpha admin confirms Globe appointment (wrong tenant + right role) → 404
# Even with TenantAdmin role, the appointment is invisible due to EF filter.
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/{{globeApptId}}/confirm
Authorization: Bearer {{alphaAdminToken}}

###
# ❌ Expected 404 — appointment not found in alpha's tenant scope
# ✓ Double defence: role check passes, then EF filter blocks → 404

### F4. Unauthenticated user reads appointments → 401
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/tenant/{{globeTenantId}}

###
# ❌ Expected 401 Unauthorized — [Authorize] on AppointmentsController
